You can find the Kea parrot in the alpine regions of New Zealand’s South Island. Kea parrots are known to be very smart and mischievous, and incredibly rare. Have you seen a parrot like this before?

📍New Zealand

node.text:
A mystical moment via @im_yash_m. 😮 Seeing the water rise up, imagine how strong and powerful the winds must have been at this moment. 💦

The Kalu Waterfall is the highest and largest waterfall in the Malshej Ghat Region, a popular destination for weekend travelers. You'll feel as if you’re transported into an outdoor adventure film here—think of surreal landscapes and the unadulterated sound of nature. 🍃

How amazing is this waterfall? What else are the best places in India for nature lovers? 🇮🇳

📽 @im_yash_m
📍 Kalu Waterfall, Malshej Ghat, India
🎶 Two Feet - Quick Musical Doodles

node.text:
💙🌲 Incredible blues from the waters of the Canadian #RockyMountains.

If you've been following us for a while, you likely know that the vibrant #blue color of #Canadian lakes is due to rock flour in the water. Rock flour is produced by the movement of #glaciers or boulders that cause rock surfaces to grind against one another. Because the rock flour is very lightweight, it remains suspended in the water. This then scatters sunlight to produce that famous blue color, the same way dust in the atmosphere makes our skies look blue.

Photo by @mitch_explores

node.text:
Sunset goals 💜 Cornwall is a county on England’s rugged southwestern tip. It forms a peninsula encompassing wild moorland and hundreds of sandy beaches, culminating at the promontory Land’s End. 

The south coast, dubbed the Cornish Riviera, is home to picturesque harbour villages such as Fowey and Falmouth. The north coast is lined with towering cliffs and seaside resorts like Newquay, known for surfing.

Where did you witness the most beautiful sunset you have ever seen? 🌅

📽 @liv_jaynex 
📍Cornwall, United Kingdom
🎶 Matt Hansen - Yellow

node.text:
Postcards from Turkey 🍃 Have you ever been to this beautiful country before?

Turkey has 44 national parks that look after its stunning natural heritage – so if you decide to visit, you’ll have plenty of options to choose from (some of our favourites are the Yedigoller National Park and the Saklikent Milli Park). 🌳🇹🇷

📍Turkey

Photos by @cumacevikphoto
